ORDataProcessor::EReturnCode ORVTreeWriter::EndRun (  )  [virtual]

End decoding the current file. Writes the tree to the output file.

Empty trees are not written to the root file if the flag fSaveOnlyNonemptyTrees is set to true. (This behaviour was implemented for ORKatrinFLTEnergyTreeWriter and ORKatrinFLTWaveformTreeWriter and was moved back to the base class ORVTreeWriter in 2008-07-25.)

Reimplemented from ORDataProcessor.

virtual void ORVTreeWriter::SetSaveNonemptyTrees ( bool  saveNonemptyTrees = true  )  [inline, virtual]

Empty trees are written by TreeWriters to the root file, if this is set to true. Setting this to false won't write empty trees to root files - this will avoid lot of empty trees in the root file.
